---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What are the rules for Discord usernames?",
    answer: "Discord usernames must contain only lowercase letters (a-z), numbers (0-9), underscores (_), and periods (.). They must be between 2 and 32 characters long, and cannot contain spaces, capital letters, or consecutive periods (..)."
  },
  {
    question: "How does the Display Name differ from the Username on Discord?",
    answer: "Your Username is globally unique, lowercase, and used to log in or add friends (e.g. @shadow_gamer). Your Display Name is non-unique, can contain capital letters, emojis, and spaces, and is what other users see in servers (e.g. Shadow Gamer 🔥)."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I use special characters in my Discord username?",
    answer: "No, Discord does not allow special characters (like !, @, #, $, %, etc.) or spaces in usernames. Only underscores (_) and periods (.) are allowed as separators."
  },
  {
    question: "Is there a limit on how often I can change my Discord username?",
    answer: "Yes, Discord limits username changes to prevent abuse. Typically, you can change your username twice within a 2-hour window."
  },
  {
    question: "Are usernames generated by this tool guaranteed to be available?",
    answer: "While this generator crafts unique username variations using standard prefix and suffix combinations, availability changes constantly. You will need to check the username inside the Discord app to confirm availability."
  }
];
---

<ToolLayout
  title="Discord Username Generator - Cool & Unique Name Ideas"
  description="Generate cool, unique, and search-friendly usernames for Discord. Customize names by aesthetic, gaming, cyberpunk, and cute niches."
  toolName="Discord Username Generator"
  toolDescription="Create unique, Discord-compliant usernames. Customize by niche styles and format preferences, verify rules, and preview on a profile card."
  category="Writing Tools"
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <div slot="calculator" class="calc-card glass">
    <!-- Main Advanced Grid Layout -->
    <div class="calc-grid">
      <!-- Left Column: Generator Inputs -->
      <div class="calc-form-column">
        <div class="calc-form">
          <!-- Seed Keyword Input -->
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="seed-input" class="icon-label">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="field-icon">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.75 5.25a3 3 0 0 1 3 3m3 0a6 6 0 0 1-7.029 5.912c-.563-.097-1.159.026-1.563.43L10.5 17.25H8.25v2.25H6v2.25H2.25v-2.818c0-.597.237-1.17.659-1.591l6.499-6.499c.404-.404.527-1 .43-1.563A6 6 0 1 1 21.75 8.25Z" />
              </svg>
              Seed Keyword / Name
            </label>
            <input type="text" id="seed-input" class="form-input" placeholder="e.g. shadow, neon, alex" value="cyber" />
          </div>

          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1rem;">
            <!-- Username Style Niche -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="style-select" class="icon-label">Niche Style</label>
              <select id="style-select" class="form-input" style="height: 48px; background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 0 12px; color: var(--color-text);">
                <option value="cyber">Cyberpunk / Tech</option>
                <option value="gaming">Gaming / Esports</option>
                <option value="cozy">Aesthetic / Cozy</option>
                <option value="cute">Cute / Soft</option>
                <option value="minimalist">Minimalist</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <!-- Formatting Dropdown -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="format-select" class="icon-label">Format Style</label>
              <select id="format-select" class="form-input" style="height: 48px; background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 0 12px; color: var(--color-text);">
                <option value="clean">Clean (Prefix/Suffix)</option>
                <option value="underscore">Underscores (_)</option>
                <option value="period">Periods (.)</option>
                <option value="numbers">With Suffix Numbers</option>
              </select>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Actions -->
          <div class="form-actions">
            <button type="button" id="generate-btn" class="calc-btn">Generate Usernames</button>
            <button type="button" id="reset-btn" class="calc-btn-secondary">Reset Inputs</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right Column: Live Mockup Card -->
      <div class="calc-editor-column">
        <!-- Live Discord Profile Mockup Card -->
        <div class="discord-profile-card glass" style="background: #18191c; color: #ffffff; border-radius: 16px; overflow: hidden; max-width: 320px; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%; border: 1px solid #202225; text-align: left; box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);">
          <!-- Top Banner -->
          <div id="discord-banner" style="background: #5865f2; height: 60px; width: 100%;"></div>

          <!-- Avatar & Badge Area -->
          <div style="position: relative; padding: 0 1rem; margin-top: -30px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: flex-end;">
            <!-- Avatar Container with Status Circle -->
            <div style="position: relative; display: inline-block;">
              <div style="width: 66px; height: 66px; border-radius: 50%; background: #2f3136; border: 6px solid #18191c; overflow: hidden; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: #ffffff;">D</div>
              <div id="discord-status-dot" style="position: absolute; bottom: 2px; right: 2px; width: 15px; height: 15px; border-radius: 50%; background: #43b581; border: 3px solid #18191c;" title="Status: Online"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Badge Box -->
            <div style="background: #2f3136; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 4px; display: flex; gap: 4px; align-items: center; font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; color: #b9bbbe; margin-bottom: 4px;">
              <span>Online Status</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Profile Body -->
          <div style="padding: 1rem;">
            <!-- Name Header -->
            <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid #202225; padding-bottom: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
              <div id="mockup-display-name" style="font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 800; color: #ffffff;">Cyber Spark</div>
              <div id="mockup-username" style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: #b9bbbe; margin-top: 2px;">@cyberspark</div>
            </div>

            <!-- Custom Info Block -->
            <div style="font-size: 0.78rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; color: #b9bbbe;">
              <div>
                <strong style="color: #ffffff; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 0.68rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">About Me</strong>
                <span id="discord-bio-text">Customizing my server settings. Add me to chat! 🎮</span>
              </div>

              <div>
                <strong style="color: #ffffff; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 0.68rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">Discord Member Since</strong>
                <span>July 15, 2026</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Generated Results Section -->
    <div id="results-wrapper" class="hidden" style="margin-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px dashed var(--color-border); padding-top: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-text); margin: 0 0 1rem 0; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; color: var(--color-brand);">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75 11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12c0 1.268-.63 2.39-1.593 3.068a3.745 3.745 0 0 1-1.043 3.296 3.745 3.745 0 0 1-3.296 1.043A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 12 21c-1.268 0-2.39-.63-3.068-1.593a3.746 3.746 0 0 1-3.296-1.043 3.745 3.745 0 0 1-1.043-3.296A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 3 12c0-1.268.63-2.39 1.593-3.068a3.745 3.745 0 0 1 1.043-3.296 3.746 3.746 0 0 1 3.296-1.043A3.746 3.746 0 0 1 12 3c1.268 0 2.39.63 3.068 1.593a3.746 3.746 0 0 1 3.296 1.043 3.746 3.746 0 0 1 1.043 3.296A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 21 12Z" />
        </svg>
        Suggested Discord Usernames
      </h3>

      <div class="usernames-grid" id="generated-usernames-container">
        <!-- Results dynamic content goes here -->
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div slot="about" class="editorial-content">
    <h2>Discord Username Generator: Optimize Your Gaming Identity</h2>
    <div style="margin: 1.5rem 0; background: var(--color-bg-alt); padding: 1.25rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-brand);">
      <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        🎮 <strong>Looking for branding strategies and server nickname ideas?</strong> Read our comprehensive guide on <a href="/blog/discord-username-generator-guide" style="color: var(--color-brand); text-decoration: underline;">Discord Username Ideas & Account Rebranding</a> to learn how to claim cool names, audit requirements, and design profiles.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>
      Discord has transformed how gamers, content creators, developers, and online communities communicate. With the platform transitioning away from four-digit discriminators (e.g. `User#0001`) to globally unique, alphanumeric usernames, claiming a memorable handle is more important than ever. If you are launching a new account or rebranding your profile, our free <strong>discord username generator</strong> helps you explore cool, compliant usernames that represent your online identity.
    </p>

    <h3>How to Use This Tool</h3>
    <p>
      To generate and preview unique Discord usernames, follow these simple steps:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Seed Name:</strong> Enter a base name or seed keyword in the input box.</li>
      <li><strong>Niche Style:</strong> Select your preferred brand identity (Cyberpunk, Gaming, Aesthetic, Cute, or Minimalist).</li>
      <li><strong>Formatting:</strong> Choose your separator format (Clean, Underscore separated, Period separated, or Suffix numbers).</li>
      <li><strong>Generate & Select:</strong> Click <strong>Generate Usernames</strong> to create 15 custom options. Click on any username chip to copy it.</li>
      <li><strong>Mockup Preview:</strong> Click a generated username to see it previewed instantly in the Discord user card mockup.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>What is Discord Username</h3>
    <p>
      A <strong>discord username</strong> is a globally unique identifier used to log in, add friends, and represent your account in direct messages. It must be written entirely in lowercase letters (a-z) and can only include numbers, periods, and underscores. This differs from your Display Name, which is what users see in server chats and can include capital letters, spaces, and emojis.
    </p>

    <h3>How Does It Work?</h3>
    <p>
      Our <strong>discord name generator</strong> processes your seed keyword and applies strict validation rules:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Character Filtering:</strong> Automatically converts uppercase characters to lowercase. It strips away spaces and prohibited symbols like hyphens or exclamation points.</li>
      <li><strong>Niche Suffix Mapping:</strong> Appends style-specific modifiers (e.g., `_cyber`, `.gg`, `_cozy`, `_soft`) to match your chosen aesthetic.</li>
      <li><strong>Format Safety Audits:</strong> Ensures the output has no consecutive periods (`..`), falls within the 2 to 32 character limit, and aligns with Discord's account rules.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Example Calculation</h3>
    <p>
      Let's look at how a generated username is checked against Discord's rules:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Input Seed Name:</strong> `"Alex Tech"` (Contains uppercase letters and a space)<br />
      <strong>Username Style selected:</strong> `"Cyberpunk / Tech"`<br />
      <strong>Format selected:</strong> `"Underscore Separated"`
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Rules Check & Optimization Process:</strong><br />
      ✦ Conversion to Lowercase: `"alex tech"` $\rightarrow$ `"alex_tech"` (Replaces spaces with underscore separator).<br />
      ✦ Cyberpunk suffix append: `"alex_tech_cyber"` (Adds style modifier).<br />
      ✦ Length Audit: `"alex_tech_cyber"` contains 15 characters, which is between the 2-32 limit.<br />
      ✦ Characters Check: Contains only lowercase characters `a-z` and underscores `_`. No consecutive periods.
    </p>
    <p>
      The generated username is `@alex_tech_cyber`. It complies with Discord's rules.
    </p>

    <h3>Who Should Use This Tool?</h3>
    <p>
      This <strong>free discord username generator</strong> is designed for:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Gamers & Streamers:</strong> Creating cool names for competitive gaming and streaming.</li>
      <li><strong>Community Creators & Administrators:</strong> Claiming clean names for community servers and public moderation.</li>
      <li><strong>Content Creators:</strong> Aligning their social media handles across YouTube, Twitch, and Discord.</li>
      <li><strong>Cozy & Aesthetic Niche Profiles:</strong> Exploring cute, soft, and aesthetic layouts for personal chat accounts.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

